main_text: 🌼🤍ВКУСНЕЙШИЙ КАРРИ с РИСОМ🍚🍃Очень люблю это блюдо🤤 Вы уже пробовали карри?⠀🌱💛Родные кто заберёт рецепт в закладочки - оставьте пожалуйста любой смайлик в комментариях🙋🏼‍♀️ Чтобы мы понимали какие рецептики Вам больше нравятся 📊БлагоДарим!🙏🏻⠀⠀⠀👩🏻‍🍳Автор: @themodernnonna 🍀🕵🏼‍♀️Перевод: @nastia_kaplun 🌱⠀⠀⠀⠀✅ ИНГРЕДИЕНТЫ:🟨 1 ст. л. оливкового масла или масла авокадо🟩 1 маленькая мелко нарезанная луковица🟨 3 измельченных зубчика чеснока🟩 15 стакана вареного нута — или банка консервированного🟨 ⅓ стакана томатного соуса🟩 3 - 4 ст. л. кокосовых сливок (это крем который находится поверх охлаждённой жестяной банки с молоком)🟨 Соль и перец по вкусу🟩 1/2-1 ч. л. куркумы карри по вкусу🟨 1 чашка мелко нарезанного шпината (можно замороженный)🟩 Петрушка или кинза по желанию🍚 2 чашки приготовленного риса для гарнира❤️ Настраивайте специи по вкусу⠀⠀⠀⠀✅ ПРИГОТОВЛЕНИЕ:⠀1️⃣ В сковороде на среднем огне обжарьте лук до прозрачности ~1 - 2 мин.Добавьте чеснок и жарьте еще 30 секунд.⠀⠀2️⃣ Добавьте нут томатный соус сливки и перемешайте.Добавьте специи перемешайте и готовьте несколько минут.⠀3️⃣ Добавьте нарезанный шпинат перемешайте и снимите с огня.⠀4️⃣ Украсьте петрушкой/кинзой или базиликом (по вкусу)🍃🍚 Выложите сверху на рис и наслаждайтесь🥰⠀🍃💛ПРИЯТНОГО АППЕТИТА!💛🍃• • •⠀⠀⠀▶️ БОЛЬШЕ ВКУСНЫХ ПОСТНЫХ РЕЦЕПТОВ В @BIG_VEGAN_BOOK 🌱⠀⠀⠀• • •💟С любовью @Veganstvo_Syroedenie#VegSyr#veganfood #рецепты #вегетарианец #вегетарианскиерецепты#vegan #veganrecipes #vegeterian #веган #веганскаяеда #веганскиерецепты #вкусно #вкусныерецепты  #безмолока #безяиц #веганство #веган #нут #chickpea#можновпост #веганскоекарри #карри #постныерецепты #пост #постноеменю #можновпост

main_text: La tartine du vendredi soir ELLE EST LÀ 💥Au menu : houmous et pois chiches croustillants and that's it ❤️Bon appétit Funky gens 😋📌 Pour 4 tartines il vous faut :📌 Pour le houmous :• 140 g. de pois chiches en conserve égouttés• 1/2 gousse d’ail• 2 cuillères à soupe d’huile d’olive• 1 cuillère à soupe de jus de citron• 1/2 cuillère à café de cumin en poudre• 1/4 de cuillère à café de sel📌 Pour les pois chiches croustillants :• 200 g. de pois chiches en conserve égouttés• 1 cuillère à soupe d’huile d’olive• 1/2 cuillère à café de paprika en poudre• pincée de sel📌 Pour la tartine :• 4 tranches de pain• Apéro Boules Tomate Funky Veggie• Huile d’olive• Paprika• Persil frais👉 Préparez le houmous. Epluchez et émincez l’ail. Placez tous les ingrédients dans un blender ou un robot mixeur et mixez pour obtenir un houmous bien crémeux. Goûtez et ajustez l’assaisonnement selon vos préférences. Réservez au frais.👉 Préparez les pois chiches croustillants. Rincez les pois chiches et séchez-les soigneusement avec du papier absorbant. Placez les pois chiches dans un bol et ajoutez l’huile d’olive le paprika et le sel. Mélangez pour bien enrober les pois chiches.👉 Faites chauffer une poêle. Versez les pois chiches et faites griller à feu vif pendant 5 à 7 minutes en mélangeant régulièrement jusqu’à ce qu’ils soient bien colorés. Déposez les pois chiches dans un plat et laissez-les refroidir. Ils vont devenir croustillants en refroidissant.📸 + recette : @funky_veggie#MakeTheWorldFunky 🌈La Funky Team...#tartine #houmous #chickpea #aperodinatoire #vegan #whatveganseat #mangerbien #mangermieux #mangersain #aperotime #recettefacile #faitmaison #miam #healthyfood #eatclean #sansgluten #dairyfree #reequillibragealimentaire #parisfood #healthysnack #recettehealthy #mangerbouger #mangerequilibre #mangersainement #bienmanger #gourmand #funkyveggie

{"1": {"comment_id": "funky_veggie"  "comment_text": "La tartine du vendredi soir  ELLE EST LÀ 💥
Au menu : houmous et pois chiches croustillants  and that's it ❤️
Bon appétit Funky gens 😋

📌 Pour 4 tartines  il vous faut :
📌 Pour le houmous :
• 140 g. de pois chiches en conserve égouttés
• 1/2 gousse d’ail
• 2 cuillères à soupe d’huile d’olive
• 1 cuillère à soupe de jus de citron
• 1/2 cuillère à café de cumin en poudre
• 1/4 de cuillère à café de sel

📌 Pour les pois chiches croustillants :
• 200 g. de pois chiches en conserve égouttés
• 1 cuillère à soupe d’huile d’olive
• 1/2 cuillère à café de paprika en poudre
• pincée de sel

📌 Pour la tartine :
• 4 tranches de pain
• Apéro Boules Tomate Funky Veggie
• Huile d’olive
• Paprika
• Persil frais

👉 Préparez le houmous. Epluchez et émincez l’ail. Placez tous les ingrédients dans un blender ou un robot mixeur et mixez pour obtenir un houmous bien crémeux. Goûtez et ajustez l’assaisonnement selon vos préférences. Réservez au frais.

👉 Préparez les pois chiches croustillants. Rincez les pois chiches et séchez-les soigneusement avec du papier absorbant. Placez les pois chiches dans un bol et ajoutez l’huile d’olive  le paprika et le sel. Mélangez pour bien enrober les pois chiches.

👉 Faites chauffer une poêle. Versez les pois chiches et faites griller à feu vif pendant 5 à 7 minutes en mélangeant régulièrement  jusqu’à ce qu’ils soient bien colorés. Déposez les pois chiches dans un plat et laissez-les refroidir. Ils vont devenir croustillants en refroidissant.

📸 + recette : @funky_veggie

#MakeTheWorldFunky 🌈
La Funky Team

main_text: This chickpea salad is another of my go-to dishes when I want something quick and healthy. It can be eaten on its own or as a side dish. {"1": {"comment_id": "nourishing"  "comment_text": "🙋 Would you try these?!

These chickpea fritters come together quickly and easily with a few simple ingredients. Serve as an appetizer or main and they are great for meal prep!....By @feelgoodfoodie

They can be made ahead of time and are great for meal prep! Easily made gluten free or dairy free by swapping a few ingredients!

INGREDIENTS
* 1 15-ounce canned chickpeas rinsed  drained
* ¼ cup flour of choice
* ¼ cup grated or shredded parmesan cheese or nutritional yeast
* 1 tablespoon chopped parsley
* 1 teaspoon cumin
* ½ teaspoon garlic powder
* ½ teaspoon salt
* ¼ teaspoon black pepper
* 2 tablespoons water
* 2 tablespoons oil of choice
* tahini sauce for serving

👩‍🍳 Instructions
1. In a medium bowl  combine the chickpeas  all purpose flour  parmesan cheese  fresh herbs  cumin  garlic powder  salt and pepper. Add two tablespoons of water and use a fork or masher to combine the ingredients until they are well blended.
2. Divide the mixture into 6 equal parts and form into thin patties.
3. In a large pan  heat the oil until it's shimmering. Then add the chickpea fritters and cook until browned and fully cooked through  about 2-4 minutes per side.
4. Place on a plate lined with a paper towel to absorb any excess oil  then serve with tahini sauce or any other sauce of choice.

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "themediterraneanhousewife"  "comment_text": "Nourishing lentil soup - Faki (φακή). When you need something light but filling x ⁣
.⁣
.⁣
.⁣Make yourself a bowl of Faki tonight:
2/3 cup green lentils
1 diced carrot
1 diced red onion
3 cloves garlic diced
1 bay leaf
Salt/ pepper to taste
One stall celery - chopped.
A few cups of water.
Olive oil.
Tomato paste - 1 tbsp
Rinse the lentils
Add everything into a pot except the lentils  tomato paste and the water.
Fry till the garlic is cooked and golden.
Add lentils and stir
Add enough water to cover everything - 2 to 3 cups boiled water.
Add the tomato paste
Bring to a boil
Dinner for 30 minutes.
Taste and test as you go.
I eat my lentil soup with crusty bread and vinegar. Enjoy xx
.⁣
.⁣

main_text: Falafelファラフェルひよこ豆を水に一晩つけておいて、茹でずに出来るってご存知でした？ギュッと固めるように成形し、そっとオイルに入れたら「触らない」ジーーっと見つめて我慢する。外側がカリッとキツネ色になってきたら、そっと裏返す。約12個分(4〜6人分)・一晩水に浸けて戻したひよこ豆: chick peas—400g(戻して水気を切った重さ)乾燥豆200g程度・赤タマネギ: red onion—1/2個・フレッシュコリアンダー: fresh coriander—15g・ガーリック: garlic—1片・クミンパウダー: ground cumin—小さじ1/2・コリアンダーパウダー: ground coriander—小さじ1/2・塩: salt—小さじ1/2・コショウ: ground black peppercorn—少々・薄力粉: plain flour—大さじ1〜・卵: egg—1/2個〜・サラダオイル: Sunflower or vegetable oil for deep frying---揚げ油として適宜タヒニソース・タヒニ: Tahini—大さじ3・水: water—大さじ2~3・ガーリック: garlic—1片(包丁で叩き潰す)・レモン汁: lemon juice—大さじ1・塩: sea salt—小さじ11. 乾燥ひよこ豆(200g程度)は洗って、たっぷりの水に一晩浸けておく2. ざるにあけて、よく水気を切る3. 赤タマネギとフレッシュコリアンダー、ガーリックはみじん切りにする4. ひよこ豆をフードプロセッサーにかけて、細かくする(粒が適度に残る程度)5. ボウルにひよこ豆、みじん切りにした玉ねぎ、コリアンダー、ガーリックと塩、コリアンダーパウダー、クミンパウダー、塩、コショウ、薄力粉、卵を加えてよく混ぜ合わせる。水分が足りない、あるいは水分が多過ぎる場合など、卵と薄力粉で調節してください6. 冷蔵庫で30分程度ねかせる(少し落ち着いて、成型しやすくなります)7. 直径5cm程度の平たい丸型に形を整える。ボロボロと整型しにくいが、手でギューーッと形を絞るようにして作るとうまくゆく8.180℃程度に熱したオイルで4〜5分、中まで火が通り、表面がきつね色になるまでカラリと揚げる。途中なるべく触らないこと。崩れます。9.タヒニソースの材料全てを混ぜ合わせる。塩やレモン汁で味をととのえ、水で硬さを調節して下さいピタパンにレタス、トマト、フムスやチリのピクルスなどと一緒にどうぞ#イギリス生活　#イギリス暮らし　#ロンドン生活　#ロンドン暮らし #mizguekanazawa　#中近東料理 #ファラフェル #ファラフェルレシピ #ひよこ豆レシピ #ひよこ豆　#falafel #chickpea
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mizuekanazawa"  "comment_text": "Falafel
ファラフェル
ひよこ豆を水に一晩つけておいて、茹でずに出来るってご存知でした？ギュッと固めるように成形し、そっとオイルに入れたら「触らない」ジーーっと見つめて我慢する。外側がカリッとキツネ色になってきたら、そっと裏返す。

約12個分(4〜6人分)

・一晩水に浸けて戻したひよこ豆: chick peas—400g(戻して水気を切った重さ)乾燥豆200g程度
・赤タマネギ: red onion—1/2個
・フレッシュコリアンダー: fresh coriander—15g
・ガーリック: garlic—1片
・クミンパウダー: ground cumin—小さじ1/2
・コリアンダーパウダー: ground coriander—小さじ1/2
・塩: salt—小さじ1/2
・コショウ: ground black peppercorn—少々
・薄力粉: plain flour—大さじ1〜
・卵: egg—1/2個〜
・サラダオイル: Sunflower or vegetable oil for deep frying---揚げ油として適宜

タヒニソース
・タヒニ: Tahini—大さじ3
・水: water—大さじ2~3
・ガーリック: garlic—1片(包丁で叩き潰す)
・レモン汁: lemon juice—大さじ1
・塩: sea salt—小さじ1

1. 乾燥ひよこ豆(200g程度)は洗って、たっぷりの水に一晩浸けておく
2. ざるにあけて、よく水気を切る
3. 赤タマネギとフレッシュコリアンダー、ガーリックはみじん切りにする
4. ひよこ豆をフードプロセッサーにかけて、細かくする(粒が適度に残る程度)
5. ボウルにひよこ豆、みじん切りにした玉ねぎ、コリアンダー、ガーリックと塩、コリアンダーパウダー、クミンパウダー、塩、コショウ、薄力粉、卵を加えてよく混ぜ合わせる。水分が足りない、あるいは水分が多過ぎる場合など、卵と薄力粉で調節してください
6. 冷蔵庫で30分程度ねかせる(少し落ち着いて、成型しやすくなります)
7. 直径5cm程度の平たい丸型に形を整える。ボロボロと整型しにくいが、手でギューーッと形を絞るようにして作るとうまくゆく
8.180℃程度に熱したオイルで4〜5分、中まで火が通り、表面がきつね色になるまでカラリと揚げる。途中なるべく触らないこと。崩れます。
9.タヒニソースの材料全てを混ぜ合わせる。塩やレモン汁で味をととのえ、水で硬さを調節して下さい

ピタパンにレタス、トマト、フムスやチリのピクルスなどと一緒にどうぞ

#イギリス生活　#イギリス暮らし　#ロンドン生活　#ロンドン暮らし #mizguekanazawa　#中近東料理 #ファラフェル #ファラフェルレシピ #ひよこ豆レシピ #ひよこ豆　#falafel #chickpea"}  "2": {"comment_id": "mizuekanazawa"  "comment_text": "ありがとうございますm(_ _)m　ファラフェル、外でいただいて好きになりました　ちょっと作れそうな気がしてきました💕"}}

main_text: CHICKPEA POTATO STEW 🍲This is such a hearty stew that is perfect for any lunch or dinner. I toasted some jalapeño cheddar toast to go with it but it also works with any kind of bread rice or grain. Highly recommend this recipe!Ingredients•2 Tbsp olive oil •2 cloves garlic •1 tsp grated fresh ginger•1 yellow onion •1 Tbsp curry powder •1 Tbsp smoked paprika •pinch crushed red pepper •1 tbsp fresh tarragon ripped•1 tsp dried rosemary•2 russet potatoes (1.75-2 lbs total) •1 15oz. can chickpeas •4 cups vegetable brothInstructions•Finely dice the onion mince the garlic and grate the ginger. Add the onion garlic and ginger to a large soup pot with the olive oil and sauté over medium heat until the onions are soft and transparent.•Add the curry powder smoked paprika tarragon rosemary and red pepper flakes to the pot and continue to stir and cook for 1-2 minutes more to toast the spices.•While the onion garlic and ginger are sautéing peel the potatoes and cut them into 1-inch cubes. Drain the chickpeas. •Once the spices are toasted add the potatoes and chickpeas to the pot. Pour the vegetable broth over top then stir until everything is combined.•Place a lid on the pot turn the heat up to medium-high and allow it to come to a boil. Once boiling turn the heat down to low and allow the soup to simmer with the lid in place for 45 minutes stirring occasionally.•Taste the soup and adjust the salt or other spices if desired. Serve!#shirasbites #chickpeas #chickpea #chickpeasalad #chickpeasrecipe #chickpeapotato #potatoes #potatosalad #potatosalad #potatosoup #chickpeasoup #healthysoup #healthysoups #souprecipe #souprecipes #dinnerideas #healthydinner #healthydinnerideas #easydinners #easybreakfast #quickhealthymeals #meatlessmonday
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "shirasbites"  "comment_text": "CHICKPEA POTATO STEW 🍲
This is such a hearty stew that is perfect for any lunch or dinner. I toasted some jalapeño cheddar toast to go with it but it also works with any kind of bread  rice  or grain. Highly recommend this recipe!

Ingredients
•2 Tbsp olive oil 
•2 cloves garlic 
•1 tsp grated fresh ginger
•1 yellow onion 
•1 Tbsp curry powder 
•1 Tbsp smoked paprika 
•pinch crushed red pepper 
•1 tbsp fresh tarragon  ripped
•1 tsp dried rosemary
•2 russet potatoes (1.75-2 lbs total) 
•1 15oz. can chickpeas 
•4 cups vegetable broth

Instructions
•Finely dice the onion  mince the garlic  and grate the ginger. Add the onion  garlic  and ginger to a large soup pot with the olive oil and sauté over medium heat until the onions are soft and transparent.

•Add the curry powder  smoked paprika  tarragon  rosemary  and red pepper flakes to the pot and continue to stir and cook for 1-2 minutes more to toast the spices.

•While the onion  garlic  and ginger are sautéing  peel the potatoes and cut them into 1-inch cubes. Drain the chickpeas. 

•Once the spices are toasted  add the potatoes  and chickpeas to the pot. Pour the vegetable broth over top  then stir until everything is combined.

•Place a lid on the pot  turn the heat up to medium-high  and allow it to come to a boil. Once boiling  turn the heat down to low and allow the soup to simmer with the lid in place for 45 minutes  stirring occasionally.

•Taste the soup and adjust the salt or other spices if desired. Serve!

main_text: Aquafaba (vegan) MeringueMy vegan friends and friends with egg allergies… or friends who just love meringue - this is a good one. Following my previous post making hummus and chickpea water - I’ve heard that chickpea water also known as aquafaba is an alternative to egg white when my daughter had an egg allergy. She’s actually outgrown her allergy now but I was quite excited to try make these aquafaba meringues. You can find a recipe on cookidoo to make in your Thermomix.I had my doubts as I was making these as I can definitely still smell chickpea up until the point I was putting them into the oven and thought it was going to be strange. Somehow the chickpea smell and taste disappears completely when it’s out of the oven.I had some frozen raspberries which I used to make a purée to add to the meringue for some extra zing and sweetness and they make them look pretty as well. I used cream of tartar to help stabilise the meringue as I didn’t have lemon juice or white vinegar which was used in the recipe and it worked fine.I’m pleasantly surprised with the results. The mini meringue kisses are super light crispy and have a gorgeous chewy centre too.They are so moreish - I need to make more of them.#thermomixukandireland #thermomixuk #TM6 #cookidoorecipe #vegan #aquafabameringue #freefrom #eggless #homemade #nowaste #aquafaba #chickpea #bromleymums #pettswoodmums #nowaste
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "mamaju_cooks"  "comment_text": "Aquafaba (vegan) Meringue

My vegan friends and friends with egg allergies… or friends who just love meringue - this is a good one. Following my previous post making hummus and chickpea water - I’ve heard that chickpea water  also known as aquafaba  is an alternative to egg white when my daughter had an egg allergy. She’s actually outgrown her allergy now  but I was quite excited to try make these aquafaba meringues. You can find a recipe on cookidoo to make in your Thermomix.

I had my doubts as I was making these as I can definitely still smell chickpea up until the point I was putting them into the oven and thought it was going to be strange. Somehow  the chickpea smell and taste disappears completely when it’s out of the oven.

I had some frozen raspberries which I used to make a purée to add to the meringue for some extra zing and sweetness  and they make them look pretty as well. I used cream of tartar to help stabilise the meringue as I didn’t have lemon juice or white vinegar which was used in the recipe and it worked fine.

I’m pleasantly surprised with the results. The mini meringue kisses are super light  crispy and have a gorgeous chewy centre too.
They are so moreish - I need to make more of them.

#thermomixukandireland #thermomixuk #TM6 #cookidoorecipe #vegan #aquafabameringue #freefrom #eggless #homemade #nowaste #aquafaba #chickpea #bromleymums #pettswoodmums #nowaste"}}

main_text: ✨️ČOKO PENA Z AQUAFABY✨️Alebo inak vyšľahaná pena vody z cicerového nálevu. Áno aj prebytočnéá voda z konzervy cíceru sa dá využiť.A ešte ako lahodne.Dokážem si predstaviť tvoj výraz pri predstave čo to je vlastne je ?! 🤨😳Moja reakcia bola tiež podobná ale veľmi rýchlo som zmenila názor po príprave tohto dezertu. 😋😄Ide o vegánsky dezert ktorý je robený rovnako ako klasická čoko pena z vaječných blielkov.Určite je vhodné osadiť si život nie len počas dňa matiek.Máme krásny máj lásky čas tak poďme na to. 😊Jeho príprava je naozaj jednoduchá🌪 a verím že touto pochúťkou ohúriš nejednu návštevu. 👌💯Pridaj kúsok maškrty od @ppress_ska dokonalý dezert je na svete.Na 4 porcie budeš potrebovať:📝🔸️Nálev z 1 konzervy cíceru🔸️Dva pásiky kvalitnej tmavej čokolády ja som použila 80%🔸️1 PL kokosový olej🔸️Dr.Gerard Choco Cool Cream tie od @ppress_sk➡️Cícer sceď a daj bodom odkvapkať prebytočnú vodu.Zatiaľ si roztop na malom ohni čokoládu s olejom a nechaj ju úplne vychladnúť.Vodu z cicera šľahaj so štipkou soli na vysokých otáčkach presne ako bielka z vajíčka cca 10 minút.Potom postupne do peny vylej čokoládu a zľahka hmotu spoj. ( už nie mixérom)Nezľakni sa pena trochu klesne a zredne.Potom už len penu vylej do pohárov a nechaj cca 3 hodiny v chladničke ql3bo cez noc. Pred podávaním poháre ozdob. Ja som použila kokosový chips jahody mrazom sušené a maškrtu Dr.Gerard Choco Cool Cream od @ppress_sk🎊Prajemj ti dobrú chuť 🎊#tvorimsDrGerard #sdrgerardomviacspolu#drgerard #ppress#ppress_sk #yummy#masktime #sladkosti#cokolada #aquafaba #chickpeas #chickpea #dezert #chocolatelover #chocolate #foodie #sweets #healthyfood #vegan #vegandessert #veganfood #veganske #yum #photo #dnesjem #fitjedlo #fittfood #mnam #healthy #fittnes

Alebo inak vyšľahaná pena vody z cicerového nálevu. Áno aj prebytočnéá voda z konzervy cíceru sa dá využiť.

comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "thecrookedrabbit"  "comment_text": "Haha! #cantstopwontstop

Chickpea pancakes 🤤
… with fresh mango and blood oranges!

Incase you haven’t seen my last several posts:

Chickpea flour
Dash salt
Dash baking soda
Garam masala
Ground ginger
this time I added ground cinnamon and some light brown sugar
Oat milk
Water

… enough liquid to make batter thin and somewhat runny

Pour batter on coconut oil greased griddle on medium heat

Top with vegan butter (or not)
Fresh mango slices
Drizzle blood orange all over
Cut up some orange slices
Shake a little powdered sugar (or not)

Sip an oat milk latte with the pancake

Enjoy!

main_text: Yesterday I had friends from work round for a totally #Vegan BBQ!I made homemade ‘Beef’ Burgers and Vegan Barbecue Spare Ribs along with grilled chilli and sesame asparagus.My friend said they wanted a totally vegan bbq and that’s what they got from flatbreads hummus and baba ganoush tabbouleh and then for dessert a vegan tiramisu!The burgers are made from a mixture of jackfruit and chickpeas and the ribs jackfruit. main_text: Sunday Snack: Do you like hummus? Do you find them hard to digest?Making hummus is a great high protein snack and is very easy to make.It is simply a case of blending chickpeas lemon juice olive oil tahini garlic salt etc in a blender.However there are a few tricks to make it tastier and easier to digest.1. Toast some sesame seeds for a richer and fuller flavour2. Add cumin paprika and cayenne for more of a spice richness and to help digestion.3. Roast your garlic prior for a more pungent garlic flavour and for a great antioxidant.4. Use sprouted chickpeas rather than tinned chickpeas as they are easier to digest and higher in nutrients.This is a photo of some hummus a made for a health retreat a little while ago with a spiral of saffron 😊Yummy 😍#sundaysnack #hummus #hummusrecipe #chickpea #digestion #garlic #ketodiet #veganfood #vegetarian #glutenfree #wheatfree #dairyfree #naturalchef #nutritionist #healthcoach #adidibite #didi #tipsdiet #foodhacks #protein #sprouted
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "a_didi_bite"  "comment_text": "Sunday Snack: Do you like hummus? Do you find them hard to digest?

Making hummus is a great high protein snack and is very easy to make.

It is simply a case of blending chickpeas  lemon juice  olive oil  tahini  garlic  salt etc in a blender.

However there are a few tricks to make it tastier and easier to digest.
1. Toast some sesame seeds for a richer and fuller flavour
2. Add cumin  paprika and cayenne for more of a spice richness and to help digestion.
3. Roast your garlic prior for a more pungent garlic flavour and for a great antioxidant.
4. Use sprouted chickpeas rather than tinned chickpeas as they are easier to digest and higher in nutrients.

This is a photo of some hummus a made for a health retreat a little while ago with a spiral of saffron 😊

Yummy 😍

#sundaysnack #hummus #hummusrecipe #chickpea #digestion #garlic #ketodiet #veganfood #vegetarian #glutenfree #wheatfree #dairyfree #naturalchef #nutritionist #healthcoach #adidibite #didi #tipsdiet #foodhacks #protein #sprouted"}  "2": {"comment_id": "a_didi_bite"  "comment_text": "@a_didi_bite thank you for sharing 😊"}  "3": {"comment_id": "mygbe1"  "comment_text": "@mygbe1 - you are welcome 🙏🏻"}  "4": {"comment_id": "a_didi_bite"  "comment_text": "Please check DM ❣️💌📩📩📩😍😍😍😍"}  "5": {"comment_id": "kethi.lovr"  "comment_text": "Love hummus and how wonderful to add saffron 😍"}  "6": {"comment_id": "saffra.coco"  "comment_text": "@saffra.coco yes thank you - makes it look 👀 pretty too 😊"}  "7": {"comment_id": "a_didi_bite"  "comment_text": "@a_didi_bite It really does 😍"}}

main_text: Yesterday I celebrated International Hummus Day with this homemade jalapeño hummus. Once I started making my own hummus I haven’t gone back to buying it. It’s so easy! My spicy hummus makes the perfect dip for veggies and is also great spread on sandwiches or with pita chips. See the recipe below.Ingredients:- 1 can (15 oz) drained garbanzobeans (chickpeas) with liquidreserved- 3 Tbsp tahini- 1 clove garlic- 1 fresh jalapeño (remove theseeds and membrane for lessspicy hummus)- 2 Tbsp fresh lemon juice- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro leaves- 1/3 tsp saltInstructions:- Place drained garbanzo beans1/4 cup of the canning liquidtahini and lemon juice in foodprocessor or blender and blenduntil smooth.- Add garlic cilantro salt andjalapeño and continue blendinguntil smooth. I like my hummusspicy so I include the membraneand seeds of the jalapeño. For aless spicy version remove themembrane and seeds beforeblending.- Serve with dippers of your choiceor use as a spread for wraps andsandwiches. This makes about 2cups of hummus and should bestored in the refrigerator.#internationalhummusday #hummusday #hummus #hummusrecipe #jalapenohummus #spicyhummus #jalapeno #jalapeño #vegetarian #vegetarianrecipes #glutenfree #glutenfreerecipes #vegan #veganrecipes #plantprotein #eattherainbow #eatyourveggies #dip #spread #garbanzos #garbanzobeans #garbanzo #chickpeas #chickpea #healthysnack #healthysnackideas #healthysnacking #healthyrecipes #healthyrecipe #plantbased
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "marinrosewatts"  "comment_text": "Yesterday  I celebrated International Hummus Day with this homemade jalapeño hummus. Once I started making my own hummus  I haven’t gone back to buying it. It’s so easy! My spicy hummus makes the perfect dip for veggies and is also great spread on sandwiches or with pita chips. See the recipe below.

Ingredients:

- 1 can (15 oz) drained garbanzo
beans (chickpeas) with liquid
reserved

- 3 Tbsp tahini

- 1 clove garlic

- 1 fresh jalapeño (remove the
seeds and membrane for less
spicy hummus)

- 2 Tbsp fresh lemon juice

- 1/4 cup fresh cilantro leaves

- 1/3 tsp salt

Instructions:

- Place drained garbanzo beans 
1/4 cup of the canning liquid 
tahini  and lemon juice in food
processor or blender and blend
until smooth.

- Add garlic  cilantro  salt  and
jalapeño and continue blending
until smooth. I like my hummus
spicy  so I include the membrane
and seeds of the jalapeño. For a
less spicy version  remove the
membrane and seeds before
blending.

- Serve with dippers of your choice
or use as a spread for wraps and
sandwiches. This makes about 2
cups of hummus and should be
stored in the refrigerator.

Serve it as a salad side dish or snack.Safiya#chanachaat #chana #chaat #chanachat #chanaaloo #papdichaat #chanamasala #chickpearecipes #chickpea #brownchickpeas #aloochaat #chickpeasalad #indianfood #indianrecipes #kalachana #f52grams #ndtvfood #buzzfeast #feedfeed
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "feastwithsafiya"  "comment_text": "Got chickpeas and potatoes on hand? Make this quick and easy Indian Chickpea & Potato salad. Delicious  refreshing  and out of this world delicious 😋.

-2 cups boiled desi chickpeas
-1 cup boiled chopped potatoes
-1/3 cup diced onion
-1/2 cup diced tomato
-1/4 cup tamarind chutney
-1/4 cup chopped cilantro
-2 tbsp diced green chili(like Thai  Serrano  or jalapeno)
-1 tsp Kashmiri chili powder  1/2 tsp for mildly spicy
-1/2 tsp roasted cumin powder
-1/2 tsp amchur powder or chaat masala  1 tsp for a good desi kick
-1 tsp salt (Himalayan pink or black salt)

1. Combine all the ingredients in a large prep bowl. Toss everything well until well combined.
2. Serve it as a salad  side dish  or snack.

Safiya
